{"id":8443,"date":"2025-09-22T06:58:03","date_gmt":"2025-09-22T06:58:03","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/realtrips.in\/?post_type=trip&#038;p=8443"},"modified":"2025-12-04T11:30:17","modified_gmt":"2025-12-04T11:30:17","slug":"assam-meghalay","status":"publish","type":"trip","link":"https:\/\/realtrips.thefuturecity.in\/trip\/assam-meghalay\/","title":{"rendered":"ASSAM MEGHALAY"},"content":{"rendered":"","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"","protected":false},"author":1,"featured_media":8919,"comment_status":"open","ping_status":"closed","template":"","destination":[86],"activities":[],"trip_types":[75],"difficulty":[],"trip_tag":[],"wptravelengine_custom_taxonomy_tripcategory":[77],"class_list":["post-8443","trip","type-trip","status-publish","has-post-thumbnail","hentry","destination-two-sisters","trip_types-customized-domestic-tour","tripcategory-customized-domestic-tour"],"packages_ids":[8444],"trip_extras":[],"cut_off_time":{"enabled":false,"duration":0,"duration_unit":"days"},"booked-seats":[],"code":"WTE-8443","price":38777,"has_sale":false,"sale_price":0,"discount_percent":0,"currency":{"code":"INR","symbol":"&#8377;"},"duration":{"days":7,"nights":6,"duration_unit":"days","duration_type":"days"},"min_pax":1,"max_pax":"","discount_value":0,"discount_label":"&#8377;0 Off","primary_category":27,"available_times":{"type":"default","items":["2021-1-01","2021-2-01","2021-3-01","2021-4-01","2021-5-01","2021-6-01","2021-7-01","2021-8-01","2021-9-01","2021-10-01","2021-11-01","2021-12-01"]},"description":"<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Two Sisters: Assam \u2013 Meghalaya<\/strong><br>Explore the unmatched beauty of the North East with a journey through the \u201cTwo Sisters\u201d \u2013 <strong>Assam and Meghalaya<\/strong>. Begin in Assam, where you\u2019ll discover the sprawling tea gardens, vibrant culture, and the world-famous <strong>Kaziranga National Park<\/strong>, home to the one-horned rhinoceros. Cruise along the mighty <strong>Brahmaputra River<\/strong> and soak in Assam\u2019s traditional charm. Continue to Meghalaya, the \u201cAbode of Clouds,\u201d where nature unfolds in its purest form \u2013 from the magical <strong>living root bridges of Cherrapunji<\/strong> and the crystal-clear waters of <strong>Dawki River<\/strong> to the stunning waterfalls and Asia\u2019s cleanest village, <strong>Mawlynnong<\/strong>. This journey blends wildlife, culture, and natural wonders, making it an unforgettable North East adventure.<\/p>\n<!-- \/wp:paragraph -->","cost_includes":"3 star premium hotel stay\nAll transfers and sightseeing by AC Vehicle.\n Breakfast, Dinner,Lunch\n Toll Tax.\n Parking.\n Driver Allowance.\n Travel Goodies\n 24 x 7 On tour Assistance\n All cost from EX Destination","cost_excludes":"Any meals other than those mentioned above inclusion\nAirfare \/ Train Ticket\n GST 5%\nAll monument entry Fees\nAny portage at airports and hotels, tips, insurance, wine, mineral water, telephone charges, and all items of personal nature.\nAny services not specifically mentioned in the inclusions.\nEntrance fees to Monuments & other sight-seeing points.\n Expenses caused by factors beyond our control like rail and flight delays, roadblocks, vehicle malfunctions, political disturbances etc.\n Anything Not mentioned in inclusions","itineraries":[],"faqs":[{"title":"1. What are the major highlights of this trip? ","content":"<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Assam: Kaziranga National Park safari, tea gardens, Brahmaputra River cruise. Meghalaya: Shillong, Cherrapunji waterfalls, living root bridges, Dawki\u2019s crystal-clear river, Mawlynnong (Asia\u2019s cleanest village).<\/p>\n<!-- \/wp:paragraph -->"},{"title":"2. Is the trip suitable for families and senior citizens? ","content":"<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Yes, the itinerary is family-friendly. However, some places in Meghalaya (like root bridge treks) involve walking\/climbing, so those with mobility issues may opt out.<\/p>\n<!-- \/wp:paragraph -->"},{"title":"3. What should I pack for this trip? ","content":"<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Light woolens (especially for Shillong &amp; Cherrapunji evenings)<br>Comfortable walking shoes Raincoat\/umbrella (Meghalaya often has sudden showers) <br>Sunscreen, sunglasses, personal medicines <br>Camera\/binoculars for safaris &amp; scenic views<\/p>\n<!-- \/wp:paragraph -->"},{"title":"4. Do I need permits or special documents? ","content":"<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>No special permits are required for Indians. Carry a valid government photo ID (Aadhar, Passport, Driving License) for hotel check-ins and safaris.<\/p>\n<!-- \/wp:paragraph -->"}],"is_featured":false,"featured_image":{"width":1013,"height":671,"file":"2025\/09\/2-4.png","filesize":1056838,"sizes":{"medium":{"file":"2-4-300x199.png","width":300,"height":199,"filesize":48639,"mime_type":"image\/png","source_url":"https:\/\/realtrips.thefuturecity.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2025\/09\/2-4-300x199.png"},"thumbnail":{"file":"2-4-150x150.png","width":150,"height":150,"filesize":21560,"mime_type":"image\/png","source_url":"https:\/\/realtrips.thefuturecity.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2025\/09\/2-4-150x150.png"},"medium_large":{"file":"2-4-768x509.png","width":768,"height":509,"filesize":221090,"mime_type":"image\/png","source_url":"https:\/\/realtrips.thefuturecity.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2025\/09\/2-4-768x509.png"},"trip-thumb-size":{"file":"2-4-374x226.png","width":374,"height":226,"filesize":65822,"mime_type":"image\/png","source_url":"https:\/\/realtrips.thefuturecity.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2025\/09\/2-4-374x226.png"},"destination-thumb-size":{"file":"2-4-600x671.png","width":600,"height":671,"filesize":217246,"mime_type":"image\/png","source_url":"https:\/\/realtrips.thefuturecity.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2025\/09\/2-4-600x671.png"},"destination-thumb-trip-size":{"file":"2-4-410x250.png","width":410,"height":250,"filesize":76170,"mime_type":"image\/png","source_url":"https:\/\/realtrips.thefuturecity.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/20